[SN]TITLE[SN]
Thirty-two arrested in Huddersfield child sex inquiry

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Thirty men and two women have been arrested as part of an investigation into historic child sex abuse in Huddersfield.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
West Yorkshire Police said 16 women had reported being abused between the ages of 11 and 18. The suspects were aged in their late teens and 40s at the time.
Addresses were searched in Huddersfield, Slaithwaite, Dewsbury and Bradford during a four-day police operation.
All 32 have been released on bail.
